@flexiarg forward-model/seal-the-graduation-criteria
@title Seal The Graduation Criteria
@sigils [⟡/?]
@audience futon stack operators, agents, forward-model authors
@tone conjectural
@style pattern

! conclusion: Pre-register and seal the criteria by which a strategy graduates, before any evidence, so neither the agents nor the loop can move the bar.

  + context: Forward-model hypothesis, not yet attested. The anti-gaming lock on graduate-strategy-by-outcome; the sealed-preregistration discipline of the flight harness, lifted to strategy.

  + IF:
    Strategic hypotheses can graduate to attested facts on accumulated outcome-evidence.

  + HOWEVER:
    If the graduation criteria are editable, the War Machine agents can devise strategy by lowering the bar to admit whatever they produced, laundering hypotheses into facts.

  + THEN:
    Seal the criteria in advance: a fixed, named threshold committed before any evidence. For example, three independent attestations of the pattern plus one discrete, externally-verifiable milestone, tiger mountain taken. The seal binds the answer key, not the candidate pool: agents may pursue the milestone but cannot rewrite what counts as reaching it.

  + BECAUSE:
    An unsealed bar is no bar. Sealing is the same anti-laundering move the flight preregistration already uses, applied to strategy: it removes the one degree of freedom an optimiser would exploit, so a graduation means the strategy actually held in the world.

    + evidence: Bridge target, not yet attested. Would reuse the sealed flight preregistration, the held-out answer-key protocol, and the three mechanical anti-false-pass detectors from the zaif harness.
